## Multi Image Source Field

An ordered list of images in one field. `images` is a `containsMany(ImageSourceField)`, so every entry supports the same URL-or-linked-file sourcing as the single Image Source field, and the two fields share one data model per image.

### Fields

| name | type | notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `images` | `ImageSourceField[]` | ordered list; each entry is `{ url, file, sourceMode }` |
| `newImage` | `linksTo(ImageDef)` | add slot — the standard linksTo editor writes a pick here and the edit UI immediately moves it into `images` and clears the slot; it never stays populated |
| `resolvedUrls` | `string[]` (computed) | every image's resolved URL, in order |
| `primaryUrl` | `string` (computed) | the first resolved URL — the cover for consumers that show one |

### Edit UI

A gallery: a hero preview of the highlighted image on top (`object-fit: contain`), a single-row horizontally scrollable thumbnail strip (click a thumb to highlight it; each thumb has a ✕ remove; new images auto-highlight), a full-width **Link Image** bar (the real linksTo editor button — card chooser with search and Create New ImageDef), and a compact paste-URL row. Empty state is a two-panel invitation — link a workspace image, or add by URL — that stacks in narrow hosts via container query.

### Usage

```ts
import { CardDef, field, contains } from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import MultiImageSourceField from '@cardstack/catalog/fields/multi-image-source/multi-image-source';

export class Example extends CardDef {
  @field photos = contains(MultiImageSourceField);
}
```

```handlebars
{{#each @model.photos.resolvedUrls as |url|}}
  <img src={{url}} alt='' />
{{/each}}
```

### Theming

Styling resolves through `--mlt-img-*` (this editor only) → `--img-source-*` (family knob shared with the single Image Source editor — one override re-skins both) → semantic theme tokens → boxel/literal fallbacks. The accent deliberately skips the app-global `--primary`; override it via `--img-source-accent` (or `--mlt-img-accent` for just this editor).
